# Commit Conventions

## When Committing

- **Do not commit everything at once** — iterate step by step
- **One logical change per commit** — group related files, or one file per commit
- **Short message** — concise, not a long paragraph

## Message Format

```
<emoji> Short sentence
```

- Use an **emoji prefix** that matches the change
- Keep the sentence **short** (under ~50 chars ideal)

## Emoji Guide

| Emoji | Use for |
|-------|---------|
| ✨ | New feature |
| 🐛 | Bug fix |
| 📝 | Docs, comments |
| ♻️ | Refactor |
| 🧪 | Tests |
| 🎨 | Formatting, style |
| ⚙️ | Config, settings |
| 🔧 | Tooling, deps |

## Examples

- `✨ Add registration state API`
- `🧪 Add registration API tests`
- `♻️ Centralize views in app/views.py`
